  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether low-molecular-weight heparin could be
      equally or more effective than oral anticoagulation in the long-term treatment of deep venous
      thrombosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The open-label prospective randomized clinical trial compares subcutaneous LMWH
      (tinzaparin)administered for 6 months versus initial treatment using subcutaneous LMWH
      followed by oral anticoagulants given for a similar period of time in patients with proximal
      venous thrombosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
